  "local_port": 50148,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I apply driving license in Bangalore?",
  "response": "Applying for a driving license in Bangalore involves several steps. Here\u2019s a comprehensive guide to help you through the process:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Eligibility Criteria**\n- **Learner\u2019s License (LL):** Minimum age of 16 for two-wheelers (up to 50cc), 18 for two-wheelers (above 50cc), and four-wheelers.\n- **Permanent License:** Must hold a learner\u2019s license for at least 30 days before applying.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Required Documents**\nYou\u2019ll need the following documents for both learner\u2019s and permanent license applications:\n- **Form 1:** Self-declaration of medical fitness (download from the RTO website).\n- **Form 2:** Application form for learner\u2019s license or permanent license.\n- **Age Proof:** Birth certificate, passport, or 10th-grade mark sheet.\n- **Address Proof:** Aadhaar card, passport, electricity bill, or rental agreement.\n- **Passport-sized Photographs:** Recent color photos (usually 2-3 copies).\n- **Learner\u2019s License:** Required for the permanent license application.\n- **Driving School Certificate:** Optional but recommended for training.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Steps to Apply**\n#### **At the RTO (Offline Mode)**\n1. **Visit the Nearest RTO:** Locate the RTO in your area.\n2. **Submit Documents:** Hand over the required documents and forms.\n3. **Pay Fees:** Pay the applicable fee at the counter.\n4. **Learner\u2019s License Test:** Take the written test on traffic rules and signs.\n5. **Permanent License Test:** After 30 days, apply for the permanent license and take the driving test.\n\n#### **Online Mode**\n1. **Visit the Parivahan Website:** Go to [https://parivahan.gov.in](https://parivahan.gov.in).\n2. **Register/Login:** Create an account or log in if you already have one.\n3. **Apply for Learner\u2019s License:**\n   - Fill out Form 1 and Form 2.\n   - Upload the required documents.\n   - Pay the fee online.\n   - Book a slot for the test.\n4. **Take the Learner\u2019s License Test:** Visit the RTO at the scheduled time.\n5. **Apply for Permanent License:**\n   - Wait for 30 days after obtaining the learner\u2019s license.\n   - Fill out the application form on the website.\n   - Pay the fee and book a slot for the driving test.\n6. **Take the Driving Test:** Visit the RTO and pass the test.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Fees**\n- **Learner\u2019s License:** \u20b9150\n- **Permanent License:** \u20b9200\n- **Smart Card Fee:** \u20b9200 (one-time charge)\n\n---\n\n### **5. Driving Test**\n- **Learner\u2019s License Test:** A written test on traffic rules and signs.\n- **Permanent License Test:** A practical driving test to assess your driving skills.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Collecting the License**\nOnce you pass the driving test, your permanent license will be sent to your registered address via post. You can also track the status online.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Tips**\n- Practice driving regularly before the test.\n- Carry all original documents for verification at the RTO.\n- Be punctual for your test appointment.\n\nBy following these steps, you can successfully apply for and obtain a driving license in Bangalore.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
